NOTE: This program uses DevIL to load images.  Here are OS installation instructions:

Ubuntu:
	sudo apt-get install libdevil-dev

Mac (from http://macappstore.org/devil/):
	ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)" < /dev/null 2> /dev/null
	brew install devil

Windows (Mingw64 + MSYS2):
	pacman -S mingw64/mingw-w64-x86_64-devil

This program demonstrates basic lighting and textures on a complex object. 

Controls:

q           - toggle liquid
x           - toggle axes
+           - zoom in
-           - zoom out

Arrow keys  - rotate the scene
1						- orthogonal view
2						- projection view
3						- first persion view
0						- reset the camera to default position

In first person mode

Arrow UP    - move forward
Arrow DOWN  - move backward
Arrow LEFT  - turn left
Arrow RIGHT - turn right

w           - move forward
s           - move backward
a           - slide left
d           - slide right


